messages.message:
The root cause of the use-after-free is that `intern->document` (a `php_libxml_ref_obj *`) can be freed during the object lifecycle (e.g., when DOM objects are destroyed), but `dom_document_save_xml` does not check whether `intern->document` is still valid before dereferencing it. In particular, the function attempts to use `intern->document->handlers->dump_doc_to_str` after the document may have been freed, leading to the reported use-after-free.

## Patch Plan

- Before using `intern->document` (and its handlers), check if it is `NULL`. If it is, fail early (emit warning and return false).
- This check should be performed at the beginning of `dom_document_save_xml` after the `DOM_GET_OBJ`.
- This will prevent dereferencing a freed pointer, fixing the use-after-free.

## Patch

I'll add a check after `DOM_GET_OBJ(docp, ZEND_THIS, xmlDocPtr, intern);` in `dom_document_save_xml`:

```diff
@@ -1617,6 +1618,12 @@
     DOM_GET_OBJ(docp, ZEND_THIS, xmlDocPtr, intern);
+
+    if (intern->document == NULL) {
+        php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document has been freed");
+        RETURN_FALSE;
+    }
```

Now, let's generate the patch.
```diff
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1617,6 +1617,12 @@
     DOM_GET_OBJ(docp, ZEND_THIS, xmlDocPtr, intern);
+
+    if (intern->document == NULL) {
+        php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document has been freed");
+        RETURN_FALSE;
+    }
+

     libxml_doc_props const* doc_props = dom_get_doc_props_read_only(intern->document);
     bool format = doc_props->formatoutput;
```

