messages.message:
The root cause is that `dom_document_save_xml` does not check if `intern->document` is `NULL` before dereferencing it. If the document has been freed, `intern->document` will be `NULL` (or worse, a dangling pointer if not set to `NULL`), and the function will still try to access its fields, causing a use-after-free.

**The correct fix is to add a check at the start of `dom_document_save_xml` to ensure `intern->document` is not NULL before using it.** If it is NULL, the function should throw an error and return.

Here is the patch:
```diff
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1617,6 +1617,12 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry *node_ce)
     DOM_GET_OBJ(docp, ZEND_THIS, xmlDocPtr, intern);

+    if (intern->document == NULL) {
+        php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document is already freed");
+        RETURN_FALSE;
+    }
+
     libxml_doc_props const* doc_props = dom_get_doc_props_read_only(intern->document);
     bool format = doc_props->formatoutput;
```
