responded: Here is the patch addressing the use-after-free:

1. In `dom_objects_free_storage`, after freeing the document, set `intern->document = NULL;`.
2. In `dom_document_save_xml`, before dereferencing `intern->document`, check if it's `NULL` and fail gracefully if so.

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/php_dom.c
+++ b/ext/dom/php_dom.c
@@ -1454,6 +1454,8 @@ void dom_objects_free_storage(zend_object *object)
        intern->ptr = NULL;
+       intern->document = NULL;
    }
 }

--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1617,6 +1617,12 @@ static void dom_document_save_xml(INTERNAL_FUNCTION_PARAMETERS, zend_class_entry *node_ce)

    DOM_GET_OBJ(docp, ZEND_THIS, xmlDocPtr, intern);

+   if (intern->document == NULL) {
+       php_error_docref(NULL, E_WARNING, "Document is no longer valid (freed)");
+       RETURN_FALSE;
+   }
+
    libxml_doc_props const* doc_props = dom_get_doc_props_read_only(intern->document);
    bool format = doc_props->formatoutput;
```

